args: I can't believe stupid Logius dove\nheadlong into an otherworld rift just\nso he could drag me along with him!
Well, dying with him in a space-time hole\nis NOT high on my to-do list, so lemme\njust find a way to... Ah! There's the rift!
Knock it off, weirdo! If we don't get out of\nhere soon, we'll get stuck in the space\nbetween worlds!
You have humiliated me at every turn,\nand I will bear it no longer!
Ugh, he's not even listening.\nLooks like I don't have a choice...
Don't blame me for this, rat fink!\nBlame your own dumb greed!
Good, the rift is still open.\nI just need a few more...
No... NO! I was too late!\nDamn, damn, DAMN!
Just existing in here puts a heavy burden\non a body. The otherworld fragments I've\ngot will buy me...maybe a few minutes?

Poor Meene must be furious. All I ever did
was worry her and make her depressed.
And as a good buddy of mine likes to say,
that won't do. No, it won't do at all...
—eloved daughter. This isn't how I hop—\n—ould meet, but it's such a joy to see you.
There's so much I want to ask you.\nSO much. So many things to talk about.\nThings I never got the chance to say.
We feel the same, but time is short.\nWe'll have to settle for telling you the\nmost important thing.
We researched other worlds since\nlong before you were born in pursuit\nof a single dream.
That dream was corrupted along the way,\ntaken by the military to be used in war.\nBut even still, we had faith.

In the endless possibilities the otherworld
gate holds. Its power can make any dream
come true, and produce things that we
never dared imagine!
We didn't live to see that dream realized,\nbut it needn't die with us...if you wish it.
There's so little we were able to leave you,\nbut we still have faith that our dream can\nlead you to a happy future.
How happy can it be if you aren't there?\nWhat kind of future is THAT?!
Reach out to the light, Daughter.
This is...the omega key?\nThe one Logius took?
Ilia, the omega key we designed holds\nboundless possibilities.
We believed in its potential—in the future\nit might bring. That's what drove all of our\nwork, and it seems to have driven you, too.
You are our greatest joy, and all we ask\nis that you find joy in turn.
We are a part of your future still.\nJust knowing we passed our curiosity\nand hope down to you is enough for us.
But what if it's not enough for ME?\nStay with me. Teach me. PLEASE!
You will understand in time. But for now,\nit's time to go. ...Use the key, Ilia.
A happy future is waiting for you\non the other side.
Meene? So I'm...outside the hideout?\nI made it back?
Oh, I'm SO glad you're alive!
Yeah, I actually thought this might\nhave been the end.
Well, now we've all learned our lessons\nand can put this otherworld business\nto rest for good and all!
Actually, uh... I'm REALLY close to\nfinishing this key for real.

You got sucked into a space-time hole and
STILL haven't had enough?! Incorrigible!
Also, you know the army will never let
this go, correct?
Oh yeah, good point. Maybe we should\nhave this convo in a safer place.
(I don't know if those voices were my real\nparents or a hallucination, but either way,\nmy mind's made up.)
(I'll keep doing my research to build\na happy future, just like they did.)
Reporting in, sir! We searched the area\nthoroughly, but found no sign of\nMajor Logius's remains.
Our conclusion is that the witness reports\nfrom his men claiming he was pulled into\nan otherworld rift are accurate, sir.
An appropriate end for a greedy fool.\n...Well? Anything else?
We sighted a girl matching the description\nof the alchemist he was pursuing in a\nnearby city.
According to the report given by Logius's\nmen, she was supposed to have been\nswallowed up by the rift along with him.
So either your scouts are mistaken or she\nmade it back alive. And if the latter is true,\nit means she has a working key.
Ha ha ha ha! Splendid! I knew I was right\nabout that girl from the first!
Stop looking for Logius and inform the\nsearch party they are to bring me that\nalchemist immediately.
Soon, Ilia... Soon you will be mine.
